Put the mortadella in a food processor and blend until it is finely chopped. Add the crème fraîche and half the cream and continue to blend.Add the Parmesan and blend again. Gradually add the remaining cream, blending all the time, until you have a smooth paste. Season with the nutmeg and black pepper to taste – you may not want to add salt.Scrape the mixture into a bowl and smooth it over. Sprinkle on the pistachios.Toast the bread, then butter it if you like. Serve the pâté on the toast.